(15, NULL, NULL, 21, '1634461970ccsp1000 600 psd.jpg', '<span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: Rubik;\">The <b>CCSP</b> shows you have the advanced technical\r\nskills and knowledge to design, manage and secure data, applications and\r\ninfrastructure in the cloud using best practices, policies and procedures\r\nestablished by the cybersecurity experts at (ISC)².</span>', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify;line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: black; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-family: Rubik;\">The </span><b><span style=\"font-family: Rubik;\">Certified Cloud Security Professional (CCSP)</span></b><span style=\"font-family: Rubik;\">\r\ncredential denotes professionals with deep-seated knowledge and competency\r\nderived from hands-on experience with cyber, information, software and cloud\r\ncomputing infrastructure security. A CCSP applies information security\r\nexpertise to a cloud computing environment and demonstrates competence in cloud\r\nsecurity architecture, design, operations, and service orchestration.</span><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify;line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: black; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-family: Rubik;\">This </span><b>CCSP</b><span style=\"font-family: Rubik;\"> Training is a self-paced learning\r\nsolution that covers the 6 domains of the CCSP Common Body of Knowledge (CBK)\r\nin order to study for 